cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA 

This paper discusses a hybrid radio platform that combines active radio and Computational RFID (CRFID) technology. The paper focuses on the performance of the hybrid radio in terms of goodput and energy consumption. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques to optimize the performance of the hybrid radio, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the system's control and optimization, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper involves information theory to analyze the performance of the hybrid radio, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves experiments to evaluate the performance of the hybrid radio, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
